      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOP THE LOT (2) hit the ground running to score by 0.8 lengths (19.71) at this track over 350m. Drawn to take advantage of good early pace. Rates to win again. WON'T BE LONG (1) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at this track over 350m behind Hara's Max (20.16) in a Grade 6. Was in the money prior to that. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Key runner on best form. HARA'S TANK (8) settled back from out wide but wound up hard into the minor money, finishing 2.5 lengths from the winner (20.17) at Capalaba in Grade 6. Likely to be in the finish again. SCOTCH BON BONS (3) returns here with a good chance to improve on last time.",
